<section id="resistance">
    <h2>Resistance Training: The Missing Link</h2>

    <p>Most cardiac patients avoid weights. This is a mistake. Resistance training improves insulin sensitivity better than any cardio.</p>

    <h3>Simple Effective Exercises</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Push-ups:</strong> Full body engagement</li>
        <li><strong>Planks:</strong> Core and stability</li>
        <li><strong>Squats:</strong> Largest muscle groups</li>
        <li><strong>Lunges:</strong> Balance and strength</li>
        <li><strong>Pull-ups/rows:</strong> Upper body balance</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The Flow Method</h3>
    <p>Move smoothly between exercises using body weight. No need for heavy weights or gym equipment.</p>

    <div class="exercise-box">
        <strong>Sample Flow Routine:</strong>
        <ol>
            <li>10 push-ups</li>
            <li>20 squats</li>
            <li>30-second plank</li>
            <li>10 lunges each leg</li>
